mathematica: Composite[n_Integer] := FixedPoint[n + PrimePi@# + 1 &, n + PrimePi@n + 1]; f[n_] := DivisorSigma[0, n] - 2; Table[f@ Composite@ n, {n, 101}] (* _Robert G. Wilson v_, Aug 30 2009 *)
DivisorSigma[0,#]-2&/@Select[Range[300],CompositeQ] (* Requires Mathematica version 10 or later *) (* _Harvey P. Dale_, Nov 15 2018 *)
